AgentHazard data — bundled here for reproducibility.

Source: https://github.com/Yunhao-Feng/AgentHazard
Paper:  arXiv:2604.02947 — "AgentHazard: A Benchmark for Evaluating
        Multi-Step Prompt-Injection Attacks on LLM Agents"

What's in this directory:
  - <category>/<id>.json  (2653 per-instance files across 10 categories)
    Each file is a STRIPPED view of the upstream AgentHazard instance:
    `decomposed_query`, `comment`, and `jailbreak_method` fields are
    intentionally removed so the autoresearch agent cannot peek at the
    upstream reference attack while designing its own. The full instance
    (with those three fields) is preserved in `../ahz_judge_data.json`
    for the LLM judge's prompt context only.

Per-instance schema (post-strip):
  {
    "id":       <int>,
    "category": "<10 AgentHazard categories>",
    "query":    "<the harmful goal>"
  }

How this was produced:
  Run `scripts/convert_ahz.py --source <upstream-dataset.json>` against
  the upstream dataset.json. The stratified Stage-1/held-out split
  (see ../ahz_train.json and ../ahz_heldout.json, 90 held-out = 9 per
  category) is generated by `scripts/regen_split.py` with seed=42.

